/*! \page page_system_guide Hardware/Software Requirements

Note: The CPU code in HOOMD is standards compliant C++ and should compile
on any architecture, contact the developers if you need HOOMD on a
different architecture. The rest of this document assumes you want to run
HOOMD on a GPU, thus limiting the options to those systems that
support CUDA http://www.nvidia.com/object/cuda_home.html.

\section sec_hardware_req Hardware Requirements
 - \b CPU: Any x86 or x86_64 processor
 - \b RAM: At least 1GB is recommended, but HOOMD should run on systems with less.
 - \b GPU: Any CUDA capable card: http://www.nvidia.com/object/cuda_home.html
 	- \b Recommended: Tesla, 8800 GTX, 8800 GTS 512MB, 8800 GT
 - \b Motherboard: 16x PCIe slot for the graphics card. If you are installing the card
 	in a second slot, double check you motherboard manual first. Many motherboards
 	will decrease the 2nd slot to 8x with 2 cards installed. While HOOMD will still
 	run in such a configuration, it is not recommended for performance reasons.
 	
\section sec_software_user_req Software Requirements
 - \b OS: Windows XP, Linux
 	- \b Note: Mac OS X support will be available once CUDA is released for it
 	- \b Note: Vista support will be available once CUDA is released for it
 - \b Python installed: http://www.python.org
 - \b CUDA toolkit 1.1 installed: http://www.nvidia.com/object/cuda_home.html

*/

